quran[30]{c,v,t}:
  7,1,ELIF. LAM. MIM. SAD
  7,2,"A Book hath been sent down to thee: therefore let there be no difficulty in thy breast concerning it: to the intent that thou mayest warn thereby, and that it may be a monition to the faithful"
  7,3,Follow ye what hath been sent down to you from your Lord; and follow no masters beside Him. How little will ye be monished
  7,4,"How many cities have we destroyed! By night, or while they were in their midday slumber, did our wrath reach them"
  7,5,"And what was their cry when our wrath reached them, but to say, \"Verily, we have been impious"
  7,6,"Surely, therefore, will we call those to account, to whom an Apostle hath been sent, and of the sent ones themselves will we certainly demand a reckoning"
  7,7,"And with knowledge will we tell them of their deeds, for we were not absent from them"
  7,8,"The weighing on that day, with justice! and they whose balances shall be heavy, these are they who shall be happy"
  7,9,"And they whose balances shall be light, these are they who have lost their souls, for that to our signs they were unjust"
  7,10,"And now have we stabilished you on the earth, and given you therein the supports of life. How little do ye give thanks"
  7,11,"We created you; then fashioned you; then said we to the angels, \"Prostrate yourselves unto Adam: and they prostrated them all in worship, save Eblis: He was not among those who prostrated themselves"
  7,12,"To him said God: \"What hath hindered thee from prostrating thyself in worship at my bidding?\" He said, \"Nobler am I than he: me hast thou created of fire; of clay hast thou created him"
  7,13,"He said, \"Get thee down hence: Paradise is no place for thy pride: Get thee gone then; one of the despised shalt thou be"
  7,14,"He said, \"Respite me till the day when mankind shall be raised from the dead"
  7,15,"He said, \"One of the respited shalt thou be"
  7,16,"He said, \"Now, for that thou hast caused me to err, surely in thy straight path will I lay wait for them"
  7,17,"Then will I surely come upon them from before, and from behind, and from their right hand, and from their left, and thou shalt not find the greater part of them to be thankful"
  7,18,"He said, \"Go forth from it, a scorned, a banished one! Whoever of them shall follow thee, I will surely fill hell with you, one and all"
  7,19,"And, O Adam! dwell thou and thy wife in Paradise, and eat ye whence ye will, but to this tree approach not, lest ye become of the unjust doers"
  7,20,"Then Satan whispered them to shew them their nakedness, which had been hidden from them both. And he said, \"This tree hath your Lord forbidden you, only lest ye should become angels, or lest ye should become immortals"
  7,21,"And he sware to them both, \"Verily I am unto you one who counselleth aright"
  7,22,"So he beguiled them by deceits: and when they had tasted of the tree, their nakedness appeared to them, and they began to sew together upon themselves the leaves of the garden. And their Lord called to them, \"Did I not forbid you this tree, and did I not say to you, 'Verily, Satan is your declared enemy"
  7,23,"They said, \"O our Lord! With ourselves have we dealt unjustly: if thou forgive us not and have pity on us, we shall surely be of those who perish"
  7,24,"He said, \"Get ye down, the one of you an enemy to the other; and on earth shall be your dwelling, and your provision for a season"
  7,25,"He said, \"On it shall ye live, and on it shall ye die, and from it shall ye be taken forth"
  7,26,"O children of Adam! now have we sent down to you raiment to hide your nakedness, and splendid garments; but the raiment of piety - this is best. This is one of the signs of God, that man haply may reflect"
  7,27,"O children of Adam! let not Satan bring you into trouble, as he drove forth your parents from the Garden, by despoiling them of their raiment, that he might cause them to see their nakedness: He truly seeth you, he and his comrades, whence ye see not them. Verily, we have made the Satans tutelars of those who believe not"
  7,28,"And when the wicked commit some filthy deed, they say, \"We found our fathers practising it, and to us hath God commanded it\" - SAY: God enjoineth not filthy deeds. Will ye speak of God ye know not what"
  7,29,"SAY: My Lord hath enjoined what is right. Turn your faces therefore towards every place where he is worshipped and call upon him with sincere religion. As he created you, to him shall ye return"
  7,30,"some hath he guided, and some hath he justly left in error, because they have taken the Satans as their tutelars beside God, and have deemed that they were guided aright"